translated:
Högberg, Saxit Erik Mauritz, retired doctor, from Söderköping. Born December 24th, 1908 in Luleå to Ivar Mauritz H. and Anmie Johanna Lindahl. Married to Vivian Schwening in 1935. They have four children: Birgitta (born 1936), Robert (born 1938), Olof (born 1939), and Eva (born 1942). He graduated from secondary school in Luleå in 1928 and earned a medical degree from Stockholm University in 1932. He received a medical license from Stockholm University in 1937. He worked as a volunteer assistant at Seraf:las. Surgical Clinic, St. Eriks Hospital, and Luleå Hospital from 1934-1936. He worked at Seraf:las. Medical Clinic in 1936, as well as a substitute doctor at Luleå Hospital, Central Sanatorium in Sandträsk, Surgical Department at Skellefteå Hospital, Medical Department at Umeå Hospital, and Söderköping Hospital from 1937-1938. He served as an assistant doctor and for a brief period as Acting Chief Medical Officer at Söderköping Hospital from 1938-1942, including four months as Acting Chief Medical Officer from 1936-1938. He was also commissioned as a provisional doctor in the Arjeplogs, Råneå, Töre, and Sorsele districts in 1942, Acting City Physician in Arvika, provisional doctor covering a vacancy in Färila from 1942-1943, and Acting Provisional Doctor in Väddö in 1943. He has been practicing general medicine in Söderköping since 1943. He serves as Chairman of the Board of Health and Chairman of the Board of Söderköping Springwater Hospital in 1946. He is also a member of the Board of Söderköping Pistol Shooting Club. His hobbies include marksmanship and botany.

(Note: The biography for Högberg, Ragnar Birger Ferdinand, a pastor in Broddetorp, is not provided.)
